-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "main.description" "Description"
@prev "main.contact"
@next "main.copyright"

	The MicroBBS is a new, fully configurable BBS.

	It is extremely small, but still very powerful. Most functions are
	implemented out of the dust by external scripts and the builtin
	configuration capabilities. Setting up the BBS is more like an easy
	way of programming than of common configuration. This brings a
	maximum of flexibility to the sysop.

	Additionally, there are no user-levels or accountings - these things
	are useless nowadays, where there are more BBSs than users. But it
	shouldn't be to difficult to add this with scripts, if you really
	need it.

	With MicroBBS you can easy implement everything between a full featured
	BBS and a small human-user-frontend for your mailer.
@endnode
