-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.options" "General configuration options"
@prev "config.example"
@next "config.chatter"

 Log:

    This is the name of the logfile where to log callers, errors, etc.

	( Log           "BBS:MicroBBS_%Node.log" )

     This option allows the special @{"%-commands" link "config.percent" 0} to be used.

 StartCommand:

    This is the first command to start on startup of the BBS. If this is not
    specified, MicroBBS tries to start "main.menu".

	( StartCommand  "Logon.bat" )

 Prompt:

    This is a string which is used as prompt, asking the user for input.

	( Prompt        "[1A[1E%H:%M:%S> " )

    This option allows the special @{"%-commands" link "config.percent" 0} to be used.
    This option requires the @{"keyfile" link "main.registration" 0}.
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.chatter" "Chatter configuration"
@prev "config.options"
@next "config.configs"

    Here you can specify the colors to use for the chatter.

	( Chatter
	    ( SerialColor   33 )
	    ( ConsoleColor  32 )
	)

    This option requires the @{"keyfile" link "main.registration" 0}.
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.configs" "Configs configuration"
@prev "config.chatter"
@next "config.console"

    With this option you can add multiple additional configs. This option only
    works in the main-configuration-file.

	( Configs
	    ( BBS:MicroBBS.cfg.lager )
	)

    This option allows the special @{"%-commands" link "config.percent" 0} to be used.
    This option requires the @{"keyfile" link "main.registration" 0}.
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.console" "Console configuration"
@prev "config.configs"
@next "config.screen"

    This describes the size of the console, the used font and the pubscreen to
    open the console on.

	( Console
	    ( Font       "IBM.font" )
	    ( FontSize   8 )

	    ( PubScreen "MicroBBS" )
	    ( Left   440 )
	    ( Top    500 )
	    ( Width  800 )
	    ( Height 500 )
	)

    The option "PubScreen" allows the special @{"%-commands" link "config.percent" 0} to be used.

    These options require the @{"keyfile" link "main.registration" 0}.
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.screen" "Screen configuration"
@prev "config.console"
@next "config.internal"

    This describes the size of the screen, the used displaymode and the name of
    the pubscreen to open. If the screen already exists, it will not be opened.

    Hint: The console will only use this screen if the specified name and the
	  Console-Pubscreen-entry are the same.

	( Screen
	    ( Width  800 )
	    ( Height 600 )
	    ( Depth  8 )
	    ( Mode   "PICASSO:  8Bit  800 *  600" )

	    ( Name "MicroBBS" )
	)

    The option "Name" allows the special @{"%-commands" link "config.percent" 0} to be used.

    These options require the @{"keyfile" link "main.registration" 0}.
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.internal" "Internal functions"
@prev "config.screen"
@next "config.batches"

    These are the internal predefined commands.

    BatchDownload   - Sends multiple files listed in the file given as
		      argument.

	( BatchDownload "T:FullFileList.%Node" )

    Upload          - Recieves one file by zmodem-transfer and puts it to
		      BBS:T.

    ChangeMaxlines  - Ask the user for a new maximum number of lines to be
		      displayed.

    ChangePassword  - Ask the user to change his password.

    GetLine         - Reads one line from the user and writes it to the
		      specified file.

	( GetLine "ENV:MSGTO%Node" )

    GetLines        - Reads several lines from the user until he presses
		      return and writes them to the specified file.

		      Without @{"keyfile" link "main.registration" 0} this function reads only one line!

	( GetLines "T:FileList.%Node" )

    LogOn           - Starts the logon-sequence with password-check.
    LogOff          - Quits the whole bbs.

    Chat            - Starts the internal chat-module.
    Echo            - Simply puts the given line out.

	( Echo "[1;1H[J" )

    WaitReturn      - Waits for the user to press return.

@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.batches" "Batch configuration"
@prev "config.internal"
@next "config.externals"

    With batches you can define a list of commands, internal and defined ones
    ( which includes batches themself), to be executed after each other. Be
    careful, it's easy to create infinite loops by starting a batch from
    itself...

	( Batches
	    ( Logoff.bat
		( Logoff.Goodbye.txt )
		( AfterSession.ext )
		( Logoff )
	    )
	)
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.externals" "Externals configuration"
@prev "config.batches"
@next "config.menus"

    Here you can specify several external commands. They are executed
    synchronus, in-/output will not be redirected. Use "C:Run" for
    asynchronus operation.

	( Externals
	    ( SetWho.ext                "C:Echo "   %Node    %User ist online." TO T:Who.%Node" )
	)
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.spawn" "Spawn configuration"
@prev "config.menus"
@next "config.texts"

    Here you can specify several spawned external commands. They are executed
    synchronus, in-/output will be redirected. Do NOT use "C:Run" for
    asynchronus operation! Asynchronus operation is NOT possible with Spawns,
    use @{"Externals" link "config.externals" 0} for this.

	( Spawns
	    ( SearchFullNames.spw       "BBS:Commands/SearchFullNames %Node "%User"" )
	)
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.menus" "Menu configuration"
@prev "config.externals"
@next "config.spawn"

    This is the most important feature of MicroBBS.

    "Password" asks for a password before entering the menu. If the password
	       is wrong, acces is denied.
    "Before"   is executed before the Menu is entered.
    "After"    is executed after every selection.

    "Options"  defines the hotkey and the corresponding action. You can specify
	       multiple action like in the @{"Batch configuration" link "config.batches" 0}.

	       The "-" is automatically defined as the hotkey to leave the
	       menu. To avoid usage of the "-" in e.g. the main menu (which
	       has no parent) simply add the "-" as option without action.

	( Menus
	    ( Statistiken.menu
		( Password "xyz" )
		( Before Menu.Stats.txt )
		( After Menu.Stats.txt )
		( Options
		    ( I
			( Stats.SystemInfo.txt )
			( WaitReturn.bat )
		    )
		    ( U Stats.Userlist.bat )
		    ( L Stats.LastUsers.bat )
		    ( R Stats.ReBoots.bat )
		    ( W Stats.Who.bat )
		    ( - )
		)
	    )
	)
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.texts" "Text configuration"
@prev "config.spawn"
@next "config.percent"

    Here you can define textfiles to be typed during action.

	( Texts
	    ( Transfer.Upload.txt       "BBS:Texte/Transfer.Upload.txt" )
	)
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.percent" "% commands"
@prev "config.text"
@next "config.example"

    These are the percent-commands you can use in many functions:

    - %%            %
    - %Node         line-number of the BBS.
    - %Baud         baudrate
    - %User         username
    - %Connect      connect-string
    - %Calls        number of calls from user
    - %Files        number of leeched files from user
    - %AllCalls     number of total calls
    - %AllFiles     number of total leeched files
    -
    - %a short name of the weekday
    - %A full
    - %b short name of the month
    - %B full
    - %c local displaymethod of date and time
    - %d day of the month (01-31)
    - %H hour (00-23)
    - %I hour (01-12)
    - %j day of the year (001-366)
    - %m month (01-12)
    - %M minute (00-59)
    - %p local equivalent of AM or PM
    - %S second (00-61)
    - %U week of the year (sunday is first weekday) (00-53)
    - %w weekday (0-6)
    - %W week of the year (monday is first weekday) (00-53)
    - %x local displaymethod of the date
    - %X local displaymethod of the time
    - %y year without century (00-99)
    - %Y year including century
    - %Z name of the time-zone
@endnode
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "config.example" "Example configuration"
@prev "config.percent"
@next "config.options"

( @{"Log" link "config.options" 0}           "BBS:MicroBBS_%Node.log" )
( @{"StartCommand" link "config.options" 0}  "Logon.bat" )
( @{"Prompt" link "config.options" 0}        "[1A[1E%H:%M:%S> " )

( @{"Console" link "config.console" 0}
    ( Font       "IBM.font" )
    ( FontSize   8 )

    ( PubScreen "MicroBBS" )
    ( Left   440 )
    ( Top    500 )
    ( Width  800 )
    ( Height 500 )
)
( @{"Screen" link "config.screen" 0}
    ( Width  800 )
    ( Height 600 )
    ( Depth  8 )
    ( Mode   "PICASSO:  8Bit  800 *  600" )

    ( Name "MicroBBS" )
)

( @{"Chatter" link "config.chatter" 0}
    ( SerialColor   33 )
    ( ConsoleColor  32 )
)

( @{"Texts" link "config.texts" 0}
